The paper deals with submodular function maximization, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The online variant of the problem is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of competitive analysis suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant.
